The alumni association of Adeniran Ogunsanya College of Education, Oto/Ijanikin, has hailed the Governor of Lagos State, Mr Babajide Sanwo-Olu, the Speaker, Mr Mudashiru Obasa and members of the Lagos State House of Assembly for responding swiftly to the call for the upgrade of the Adeniran Ogunsanya College of Education to the University of Education, Lagos State. This was contained in a statement signed by the National Public Relations of the association, Opeyemi Eniola, titled, “Thank you Mr Governor, thank you the pro-people Lagos State House of Assembly”. The statement quoted the National President, Prince Oluwashina Akintolure, as saying that the intervention of the Lagos legislators was not only timely but also signified. “The Governor and the Lagos State House of Assembly are conscious of people-oriented progammes to bring about the needed development in Lagos state, most especially the initiation of the bill to upgrade of Adeniran Ogunsanya College of Education to a University, it read. Meanwhile, the association on Saturday, July 10 appointed a five-man electoral committee to conduct the election that will usher in new executives. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com